This paper deals with dynamic program analysis for preventing implicit information flows, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the permissive-upgrade check, which is a technique used in programming languages and software engineering (cs.PL, cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of lattices, which is a topic in mathematical logic and computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the paper deals with the development of a sound and permissive definition, which is a topic related to control systems and automation (cs.SY).
